Error: Error: "Connection Refused: Failed To Connect To Server" When Attempting To Connect To A Minecraft Server Hosted On A Pterodactyl Panel.

Solution: 1. Check if the server is running: In the Pterodactyl Panel, navigate to the server dashboard and check the status of the server. If the server is not running, start it.

2. Check the server IP and port number: Make sure that the IP and port number entered in the Minecraft client match the server
